===Etymology 1===
Traditionally thought to be related to {{och-l|疏|id=1|distant; sparse}}, as compared to {{och-l|篦|fine-tooth comb}} (''{{w|Shiming}}''; {{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}).

However, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considers this to be folk etymology and instead proposes that this is related to {{cog|bo|གཤོད||to comb}}, {{cog|tbq-kuk-pro|*hriat||to comb; to brush}}. STEDT provisionally reconstructs {{cog|tbq-pro|*srja(t)|*g-s-y(w)at|to comb; to brush}} and also notes possible connection to {{cog|tbq-pro|*m-si-t||comb; rake}}.

